    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter May 2nd with a lineup anchored by high-ceiling matchups in the outfield and infield. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (72.34) represents our strongest play today; his matchup against Ryne Nelson is bolstered by a significant dynamic platoon edge (+14%) and favorable park factors, making him a prime candidate to capitalize on his elite sprint speed. **Junior Caminero** (67.10) and **Colt Keith** (66.91) follow closely as high-efficiency starts. **Colt Keith** specifically benefits from facing the deliberate delivery of Kumar Rocker, which historically inflates stolen base opportunities\u2014a critical lever for our roster composition. Meanwhile, **Caleb Durbin** (63.88) earns a strong start despite a bottom-of-the-order slot, as his speed profile and matchup against Spencer Arrighetti create an efficient path to production despite the 33% rain risk.\n\nStrategic roster management remains focused on maximizing efficiency over raw power. The most difficult bench decision today involved **Chase Meidroth** (47.06), who just missed the cut for the starting nine. While his floor is reliable, the optimizer favored the higher platoon-adjusted ceilings of **Josh Smith** and **Luke Raley** to better balance the 5x5 categories. We are also monitoring weather patterns closely; both **Caleb Durbin** and **Yordan Alvarez** (53.88) face potential precipitation delays. **Yordan Alvarez** remains a start despite the weather and a tough matchup against the lefty Connelly Early, as his elite xwOBA (0.434) keeps his floor viable even when the park factors and SP skill metrics work against him. Outside of the active lineup, **Christian Yelich** remains sidelined on the IL, while **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Pedro Ramirez**, and **Luis Pena** are held in reserve as we await further lineup confirmations.",
